h3. Summary

When you create a post function to update a multiple valued custom field (e.g. user picker) after a transition, and check the append value option during it's creation, executing the transition multiple times will also add the same user multiple times.

If you activate the field in the view screen, it shows the user once. But if you search in the database, the *customfieldvalue* table will have a duplicated entry, with a different id, but the issue and the string value are the same. 
h3. Environment

Jira Cloud.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Click on the *cog icon* in the top right of your screen -> select *Issues*;
 # Look at the left on your screen -> select *Workflows* under the *WORKFLOWS* section;
 # Search for the workflow used by your project and click on *Edit* under the *Actions* column;
 # Once you are in, you will see it on text mode, and you can select a transition to add a post function;
 #  Select the *Post functions* section -> *Add post function*;
 # Check *Update Issue Custom Field*;
 # Select a multi valued field in the *Issue Custom Field* -> type *%%CURRENT_USER%%* in the *Custom Field Value* field, check the *Append value* option -> click on Add;
 # Don't forget to publish your draft.

After that process, create a issue and test the transition in a sprint.

You can see it has inserted the same value again in the issues' *History* section:

!Screen Shot 2017-11-17 at 4.15.06 PM.png!

 
h3. Expected Results

The user picker should insert the user just once.
h3. Actual Results

The user picker inserts the same user multiple times.
h3. Workaround

Leaving the Append value option unchecked will prevent it from happening, although it won't insert more than one value, and also replace the current user from the field.

When generating a cookie via the endpoint {{/rest/auth/1/session}}, it'd be interesting to be able to provide the API token generated at https://id.atlassian.com in the body of the request instead of the user's password. Example call being:
{code}curl -D- --silent --cookie-jar "myCookie" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"username": "<user>", "password": "<API_Token_here>"}' -X "POST" "https://instance.atlassian.net/rest/auth/1/session"{code}

This would help customer to avoid stressing the server with basic auth using tokens. But instead they could generate one without having to use their passwords.

h3. Summary

A non UTF charecter pasted to a Jira comment cause a communications breakdown in Jira

Steps to Reproduce
 # Compile the following code
{code:java}
Test.java 
public class Test 
{ 

     public static void main(String[] args) 
     { System.out.println("ABC \u0000 DEF"); } 
}{code}

 # Run the folloing command (on MAC) to add the result to the clipboard
{code:java}
pbcopy < test 
{code}

 # Paste into a Jira issue comment

h3. Expected Results

An error of non Character should be trated by Jira
h3. Actual Results

Jira throws an error of "Communications breakdown"
h3. Notes

This error in logs:
{code:java}
Caused by: org.postgresql.util.PSQLException: ERROR: invalid byte sequence for encoding "UTF8": 0x00 at org.postgresql.core.v3.QueryExecutorImpl.receiveErrorResponse(QueryExecutorImpl.java:2477) at org.postgresql.core.v3.QueryExecutorImpl.processResults(QueryExecutorImpl.java:2190) at org.postgresql.core.v3.QueryExecutorImpl.execute(QueryExecutorImpl.java:300) at org.postgresql.jdbc.PgStatement.executeInternal(PgStatement.java:428) at org.postgresql.jdbc.PgStatement.execute(PgStatement.java:354) at org.postgresql.jdbc.PgPreparedStatement.executeWithFlags(PgPreparedStatement.java:169) at org.postgresql.jdbc.PgPreparedStatement.executeUpdate(PgPreparedStatement.java:136) at sun.reflect.GeneratedMethodAccessor645.invoke(Unknown Source) at sun.reflect.DelegatingMethodAccessorImpl.invoke(DelegatingMethodAccessorImpl.java:43) at java.lang.reflect.Method.invoke(Method.java:498) at org.vibur.dbcp.proxy.AbstractInvocationHandler.targetInvoke(AbstractInvocationHandler.java:144) at org.vibur.dbcp.proxy.StatementInvocationHandler.on(StatementInvocationHandler.java:161) at com.atlassian.jira.connpool.JiraViburConnectionPoolProvider.lambda$null$5(JiraViburConnectionPoolProvider.java:149) at org.vibur.dbcp.proxy.StatementInvocationHandler.processExecute(StatementInvocationHandler.java:123) at org.vibur.dbcp.proxy.StatementInvocationHandler.restrictedInvoke(StatementInvocationHandler.java:85) at org.vibur.dbcp.proxy.StatementInvocationHandler.restrictedInvoke(StatementInvocationHandler.java:37) at org.vibur.dbcp.proxy.AbstractInvocationHandler.invoke(AbstractInvocationHandler.java:80) at com.sun.proxy.$Proxy4775.executeUpdate(Unknown Source) at com.querydsl.sql.dml.SQLInsertClause.executeWithKeys(SQLInsertClause.java:368) ... 356 more
